# Connect navaids to their associated airports
for _, row in navaids_df.iterrows():
    if pd.notna(row["associated_airport"]) and row["associated_airport"] in G.nodes:
        G.add_node(row["id"], pos=(row["longitude_deg"], row["latitude_deg"]), type="navaid")
        G.add_edge(row["id"], row["associated_airport"], weight=1)
In [9]:
# Compute nearest airport connections
airport_positions = {row["ident"]: (row["latitude_deg"], row["longitude_deg"]) for _, row in airports_df.iterrows()}
airport_coords = np.array(list(airport_positions.values()))
airport_ids = list(airport_positions.keys())
airport_tree = KDTree(airport_coords)

k = 5  # Limit to nearest 5 neighbors for better connectivity
for i, airport in enumerate(airport_ids):
    pos1 = airport_positions[airport]
    _, indices = airport_tree.query(pos1, k=k + 1)
    for j in indices[1:]:
        neighbor = airport_ids[j]
        distance = geodesic(pos1, airport_positions[neighbor]).kilometers
        G.add_edge(airport, neighbor, weight=distance)

# Centrality Analysis (Find hub airports)
degree_centrality = nx.degree_centrality(G)
closeness_centrality = nx.closeness_centrality(G)
betweenness_centrality = nx.betweenness_centrality(G)

top_hubs = sorted(degree_centrality.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:10]

def display_top_airports(metric, name):
    print(f"Top 10 Airports by {name}:")
    for airport, value in metric[:10]:
        print(f"{airport}: {value:.4f}")

display_top_airports(top_hubs, "Degree Centrality")

top_closeness = sorted(closeness_centrality.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
display_top_airports(top_closeness, "Closeness Centrality")

top_betweenness = sorted(betweenness_centrality.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
display_top_airports(top_betweenness, "Betweenness Centrality")

# Centrality Analysis (Optimized for Performance)
small_sample = list(G.nodes)[:500]  # Limit analysis to 500 nodes for efficiency
degree_centrality = {node: val for node, val in nx.degree_centrality(G).items() if node in small_sample}
closeness_centrality = {node: nx.closeness_centrality(G, u=node) for node in small_sample}
betweenness_centrality = nx.betweenness_centrality(G, k=50, normalized=True)  # Approximate with k=50

top_hubs = sorted(degree_centrality.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:10]

def display_top_airports(metric, name):
    print(f"Top 10 Airports by {name}:")
    for airport, value in metric:
        print(f"{airport}: {value:.4f}")

display_top_airports(top_hubs, "Degree Centrality")

top_closeness = sorted(closeness_centrality.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:10]
display_top_airports(top_closeness, "Closeness Centrality")

top_betweenness = sorted(betweenness_centrality.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:10]
display_top_airports(top_betweenness, "Betweenness Centrality")

# Convert centrality values to lists
degree_values = list(degree_centrality.values())
closeness_values = list(closeness_centrality.values())
betweenness_values = list(betweenness_centrality.values())

# Plot KDE for Degree Centrality
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
sns.kdeplot(degree_values, fill=True, color='blue', bw_adjust=0.5)
plt.title("Degree Centrality Distribution (KDE)")
plt.xlabel("Degree Centrality")
plt.ylabel("Density")
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Plot KDE for Closeness Centrality
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
sns.kdeplot(closeness_values, fill=True, color='green', bw_adjust=0.5)
plt.title("Closeness Centrality Distribution (KDE)")
plt.xlabel("Closeness Centrality")
plt.ylabel("Density")
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Plot KDE for Betweenness Centrality
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
sns.kdeplot(betweenness_values, fill=True, color='red', bw_adjust=0.5)
plt.title("Betweenness Centrality Distribution (KDE)")
plt.xlabel("Betweenness Centrality")
plt.ylabel("Density")
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
